"NetStream.Play.Transition" "status" Flash Media Server 3.5 and later only. The server received the command to transition to another stream as a result of bitrate stream switching. This code indicates a success status event for the NetStream.play2() call to initiate a stream switch. If the switch does not succeed, the server sends a NetStream.Play.Failed event instead. When the stream switch occurs, an onPlayStatus event with a code of "NetStream.Play.TransitionComplete" is dispatched. For Flash Player 10 and later.
